code: import pandas as pd import os import sys import subprocess import csv from collections import defaultdict # Install num2words if missing try: from num2words import num2words except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, "-m", "pip", "install", "num2words==0.5.10"]) from num2words import num2words # Build lookup table lookup = defaultdict(lambda: defaultdict(int)) chunk_size = 100000 for chunk in pd.read_csv( "input/ru_train.csv", chunksize=chunk_size, usecols=["before", "after"] ): chunk["after"] = chunk["after"].where(chunk["after"] != "<self>", chunk["before"]) chunk = chunk.dropna(subset=["after"]) for before, after in zip(chunk["before"], chunk["after"]): lookup[before][after] += 1 final_lookup = {} for before, counts in lookup.items(): final_lookup[before] = max(counts.items(), key=lambda x: x[1])[0] # Normalization function def normalize_token(token): token = str(token).strip() return final_lookup.get(token, _handle_unknown_token(token)) def _handle_unknown_token(token): clean_token = token.replace(",", "").replace(".", "").strip() if clean_token.isdigit(): try: num = float(clean_token) return num2words(num, lang="ru", to="cardinal") except: pass return token # Process test data test_df = pd.read_csv("input/ru_test_2.csv") # Create submission DataFrame submission = pd.DataFrame( { "id": test_df["sentence_id"].astype(str) + "_" + test_df["token_id"].astype(str), "after": test_df["before"].apply(normalize_token), } ) # Ensure string types submission["id"] = submission["id"].astype(str) submission["after"] = submission["after"].astype(str) # Save submission using csv module to avoid pandas version issues os.makedirs("submission", exist_ok=True) with open("submission/submission.csv", "w", encoding="utf-8", newline="") as f: writer = csv.writer(f) writer.writerow(["id", "after"]) for row in submission.itertuples(index=False): writer.writerow([row.id, row.after]) # Generate validation metric train_sample = pd.read_csv("input/ru_train.csv", nrows=10000) train_sample["pred"] = train_sample["before"].apply(normalize_token) accuracy = (train_sample["after"] == train_sample["pred"]).mean() print(f"Validation Accuracy: {accuracy:.4f}")
